Generic single-database configuration for Alembic migrations.

## Usage

### Initialize database with latest migrations

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Create a new migration after model changes

```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description of changes"
```

### Check current migration status

```bash
alembic current
```

### View migration history

```bash
alembic history
```

### Rollback last migration

```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### Rollback to specific revision

```bash
alembic downgrade <revision_id>
```

## Configuration

Database URL is automatically loaded from environment variables via `shared_config.settings.AppSettings`.

Make sure to set `DATABASE_URL` in your `.env` file:

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/knowledge_platform
```

